30|$|Research within China has mainly {{illustrated}} urban wastewater’s {{effect on}} agricultural <b>water’s</b> <b>productivity</b> from an environmental science aspect. Urban wastewater has abundant organic pollutants such as N, P, K, bacterium, parasites and viruses, {{which are the}} main source of urban water pollution. After treatment, wastewater consists of two parts: one is water, the other is sludge. Treated wastewater can be emitted directly or can be used as reclaimed water. Sludge contains parasite ova, pathogenic microorganisms, and heavy metals, and creates secondary pollution if it is not properly disposed. Both the polluted water and sludge can be harmful to water and soil if emitted or recycled without fulfilling environmental standards.|$|R
